songs.title: YKWIM?

description.plain: Have you ever felt frozen in thought because of your past experiences? If not,  this song will make you feel that way, as you are guided through the emotions that appear throughout the piece, as we recall a past relationship that soured over time. This heavenly masterpiece will get any listener in their feels as it opens the door to our most mournful and even regretful past relationships.

songs.title: Japan

description.plain: ‘Japan,’ the third track on Yot Club’s EP Bleach Beach, is a surf-rock influenced song. With drained vocals with a distorted effect, the lyrics include mention slight Japanese words, referring to the title.

songs.title: Fly Out West

description.plain: ‘Fly Out West’ is a feel good, uptempo indie lo-fi rock song with “luminous synths, swirling guitars, and twittering birds.” The lyrics describe seeking out for a vacation, and wanting to leave to a new place.
